added.title: Finding Aquaman
added.description: While searching for a missing Aquaman, the Titans find themselves at the mercy of Black Manta.

added.title: Whodundidit?
added.description: While housesitting at Wayne Manor, the Titans must unravel the mystery of the clogged toilet.

added.title: Sweet Revenge
added.description: Robin starts working at an ice cream shop to get revenge on Joker's Gelato for denying him a free birthday scoop.

added.title: Porch Pirates
added.description: After their package is stolen, the Titans must join a crew of porch pirates to get it back.

added.title: A Sticky Situation
added.description: Sticky Joe's search for a can opener leads to a series of wacky adventures.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: Lil' Dimples
added.description: Thinking it's a way to reconnect with her father, Raven enters a beauty pageant.

added.title: Demon Prom
added.description: Trigon makes Raven attend her prom and she brings along the other Titans to upset him.

added.title: Rad Dudes with Bad Tudes
added.description: After seeing a pair of cool dudes on rollerblades, Robin tries to be just like them.

added.title: Crazy Day
added.description: It's Crazy Day again and Raven must do her best to avoid being driven crazy by the other Titans.

added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Nean
added.description: Raven is cursed to be nice; meanwhile, Starfire is about to marry a pot of chili.

added.title: Dreams
added.description: A glimpse inside each Titan's dream world.

added.title: The Lady
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin track a women emerging from their home, they discover her to be a member of a gang of wise-cracking elderly friends. However, as they get closer and closer to her life, they realize they may know her already.

added.title: The Neighbor
added.description: When their neighbor tries to bring over a package for them, Gumball and Darwin realize they have never learned his name, and it's way too late to ask. They try everything to figure out what it is, but when they do they find out there are bigger secrets to learn about their neighbor than just his name...

added.title: The Slip
added.description: Richard doesn't answer the door in time and the jobsworth delivery guy will not let him have his package. His options are to pick his package up at the depot or pay for a redelivery. Richard doesn't like the sound of either option, so a battle of wills begins that can only end in the destruction of one or both of them.

added.title: The Possession
added.description: Nicole has decided it's time to throw out the family's refrigerator. This doesn't go down too well with Richard, as it's his favorite possession. When it turns out the refrigerator is also a magical storage facility for childhood emotions and memories, it makes sense that Richard is having a hard time letting go.

added.title: The Outside
added.description: The family goes to visit Richard's Dad. Based on his basic living standards and extended absence from Richard's life, they assume Frankie must have done a stretch in the slammer. When Frankie comes to stay with the Wattersons, they decide the way to make him comfortable is to make him uncomfortable and turn their house into a prison.

added.title: The Diet
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the reason Dad's diet wasn't working was that he was actually on ten diets and eating a meal for each of them. They eventually manage to help him lose weight, but Richard's newfound buffness also brings out his more obnoxious side.

added.title: The Heist
added.description: Richard discovers going into a bank whilst wearing a motorcycle helmet can land you in a lot of trouble.

added.title: The Routine
added.description: Mom and the kids depart for their hard day's work, leaving a seemingly lazy Dad half-asleep on the sofa. Mom has given him one very simple job: buy mayonnaise. However, Dad manages to turn this mundane task into an epic quest, showing that his daily routine isn't as inactive as his family imagine.

added.title: The Money
added.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

added.title: The Job
added.description: Dad gets his first job as a pizza delivery guy, which rocks the very fabric of the universe.

added.title: The Hero
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are determined to prove to their dad that he is their hero, at any cost!

added.title: The Castle
added.description: When Mom is away "anything goes" and Dad's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome houseguests.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are unwitting accomplices in a gas station robbery.

added.title: The Mustache
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's wish comes true when they suddenly turn into men.

added.title: The Other Side: The Tournament
added.description: The Tournament - Hoping to win a special prize for his Dad's birthday, Craig and his friends compete in a tournament on the Other Side of the Creek!

added.title: Craig of the Beach
added.description: Craig gets to hit the beach with his friends and family, but starts to get worried his Dad is more fun than him.

added.title: King of Camping
added.description: The Williams Family goes camping and Craig helps his dad prove he's the King of Camping.

added.title: Cousin of the Creek
added.description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

added.title: The Evolution of Craig
added.description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!

added.title: Craig and the Kid's Table
added.description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

added.title: Ancients of the Creek
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP discover an ancient fort that belonged to the first kids in the Creek.

added.title: In the Key of the Creek
added.description: When a rainy day keeps Craig inside, he uses his toys and imagination to create his own Creek adventure in Craig of the Creek's first musical episode!

added.title: The Children of the Dog
added.description: Craig has tried to convince his family to get a dog for years but has never been successful, but he may have a chance if he follows the guidance of a charismatic creek kid and her three step program.

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: Ferekh
added.description: Apple and Onion are put in charge of Falafel's beloved rooster but it turns out that other parties have a vested interest in it too.

added.title: Pat on the Head
added.description: Apple and Onion are to cook for a very important guest but Onion is not quite feeling himself.

added.title: Falafel's Glory
added.description: Apple and Onion must recruit the help of retired quiz master Falafel if they are to not starve.

added.title: Slobbery
added.description: Burger's roommate is not only a problem for him, but for Apple and Onion who need Burger's help for something else.

added.title: Microwave's Dance Club
added.description: DJ Saltfish and MC Ackee are in town for two nights only and Apple and Onion are determined to make the most of it and bust some moves on the dance floor.

added.title: All Work and No Play
added.description: Having finally saved up and aquired an expensive toy race track, Apple and Onion are faced with one problem- there is no time to play with it.

added.title: Drone Shoes
added.description: Can there exist such a thing as drone shoes? It sounds like they would need a huge power capacity.

added.title: Walking on the Ceiling
added.description: Apple's curiosity of what it would be like to walk upside down like a spider should be ignored and given no further thought. It is not.

added.title: Keep It Fresh
added.description: It's Apple's turn to buy this months' groceries again meaning that the risk of starvation is at hand.

added.title: Panamanian Night Monkey
added.description: Apple and Onion must adopt unorthodox measures if they are to see this special animal at the zoo.

added.title: Broccoli
added.description: Some major construction is taking place on the roof of Apple and Onion's building and they can't get back home till it's finished.

added.title: Cousin's Day
added.description: It's Cousin's Day- another holiday the corporations made up to make more money and Apple and Onion are going to capitalise on it.

added.title: Nothing Can Stop Us
added.description: Hot Dog has the audition of his life but he is missing something crucial. Apple and Onion are tasked with bringing it to him and they are adamant that nothing will stand in their way.

added.title: Good Job
added.description: Falafel is starting to feel very underappreciated as the building's handyman. What's the point in all this back breaking work if not a single person will ever tell him, "Good Job"?

added.title: Za
added.description: Pizza's Diner needs a makeover. Apple and Onion better get this right or Pizza is ruined.

added.title: The Demon
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear accidentally lose Chloe's prized hoodie to the ferocious dog next store. They go on a mission to get it back.

added.title: Panda's Art
added.description: Panda paints a portrait of Charlie and it's a hit with his art class. But after an art dealer offers to buy the painting, Panda has to get it back from Charlie.

added.title: Poppy Rangers
added.description: Ranger Tabes leads a troop of young girls into a cave expedition, and brings Grizz as their cave expert.

added.title: Lucy's Brother
added.description: To impress Lucy Panda offers to babysit her brother, Clifford. But Clifford turns out to be too high maintenance for Panda to handle.

added.title: The Fair
added.description: The Baby Bears make a deal with a carnival worker to be prizes for a game of ball toss.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Cellie
added.description: Fed up with sharing, Panda forbids his brothers from using his cellphone any longer. But when the brothers get their own super advanced smartphones, Panda starts to succumb to crippling jealousy.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: The Island
added.description: While trying to sail to Japan, the Baby Bears get stranded on an island. Luckily, they meet Dave and Karla, who help with survival on the island while looking for an escape.

added.title: Bear Flu
added.description: The Bears become terribly ill and Chloe takes it upon herself to take care of them. But things get tricky when word of the Bears' sickness goes viral.

added.title: Chicken and Waffles
added.description: Panda needs to meet his brothers at the most exclusive restaurant in town. But when he loses his contacts lenses and can't see, Panda needs Charlie's help to get him into the city.

added.title: The Audition
added.description: The Bears audition to be the next mascot for their favorite cereal. They get so caught up in the process that their competitiveness gets the best of them.

added.title: Captain Craboo
added.description: The Bears are reunited with their pet crab, Captain Craboo. But after an unfortunate run-in with Nom Nom, the Bears may lose their pet forever.

added.title: Baby Bears on a Plane
added.description: The Baby Bears have an adventure in the sky while aboard a plane to Sweden. But when the baby Bears are forced to sit in different sections of the plan, things get a bit haywire for everyone on board.

added.title: Gemcation
added.description: Greg and the Gems take Steven on vacation to help him relax.

added.title: The Big Show
added.description: Steven shoots a documentary that follows a local band as they get their first big break.

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Change Your Mind
added.description: Steven faces his biggest challenge yet.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Storm in the Room
added.description: Steven goes into his room in the temple to look for answers.

added.title: Hit the Diamond
added.description: Steven and the Gems play an old fashioned game of baseball.

added.title: Steven Floats
added.description: Steven is so excited to be back home that he jumps for joy and jumps way too high.

added.title: Drop Beat Dad
added.description: Steven helps Sour Cream put on a show, even though Sour Cream's stepdad doesn't approve of DJs.

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: Alone Together
added.description: The Gems try to teach Steven to use his fusion powers.

added.title: Jail Break
added.description: Steven teams up with a new ally to rescue the Gems.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: Marcy & Hunson
added.description: Hunson Abadeer returns to Ooo to bond with his daughter Marceline, but will he be able to prove that he's changed his soul-sucking ways?

added.title: Varmints
added.description: Bubblegum teams up with Marceline to face a threat to her homestead's citizens.

added.title: Escape from the Citadel
added.description: Finn and Jake follow the Lich of the Citadel, where Finn meets his long lost dad. But just how far does the apple fall from the tree?

added.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
added.description: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

added.title: Jake the Dog
added.description: Jake and Prismo watch from the portal as the Ice King's crown makes Finn more and more powerful.

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: Sky Witch
added.description: Marceline is on a top-secret mission tracking Maja the Sky Witch. When she loses the witch's trail, Marceline turns to Princess Bubblegum for help.

added.title: The Pit
added.description: Kee-Oth the Blood Demon has kidnapped Jake, taken him back to his dimension and thrown him in a pit. If Finn wants to rescue his friend, he's going to need Lady Rainicorn's help and a videotape that will reveal how to open the portal to Kee-Oth's dimension.

added.title: King Worm
added.description: Finn has a particularly vivid dream, and all of Ooo is in it or does he?

added.title: What Was Missing
added.description: Finn and Jake do battle with a powerful door lord.

added.title: Dad's Dungeon
added.description: Jake's Dad appears in a holographic message with a mysterious challenge for Finn and Jake.

added.title: It Came From the Nightosphere
added.description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo! Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

added.title: Crystals Have Power
added.description: Jake takes a vow of non-violence, which is inconvenient when they're attacked by marauders from the crystal dimension.

added.title: Go With Me
added.description: Finn needs to date to the movies and must balance the contrasting advice of Jake and Marceline in wooing Princess Bubblegum so he can see that flick!

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: A Regular Epic Final Battle Part 1
added.description: An epic final battle begins.

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Rigby Goes to Prom
added.description: Rigby asks Eileen to prom. But in order to get there, he has to sneak his Dad's car out of the garage and get it back in one piece.

added.title: Rigby's Graduation Day Special
added.description: Rigby has to give a speech at his high school graduation. The speech will be broadcast live on a TV show called Inspire America, and Rigby wants to make it memorable.

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park IV
added.description: The park guys try to keep Muscle Man awake with scary stories on a long drive so that they can meet his mom.

added.title: Sad Sax
added.description: Mordecai wants to get back together with C.J.

added.title: Dumped at the Altar
added.description: The guys have to get Muscle Man married.

added.title: Power Tower
added.description: Muscle Man wants to win the bodybuilding competition at his gym.

added.title: Family BBQ
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a handshake from Margaret's dad.

added.title: The Best Burger in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to finish their chores before they can have burgers.

added.title: Dead at Eight
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to babysit Death's kid.

added.title: Trucker Hall of Fame
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Muscle Man get to the Big Rig Museum to spread his dad's hat's ashes.

added.title: Dizzy
added.description: M and R help Pops get over his fear of public speaking.

added.title: Benson Be Gone
added.description: Mordecai sees Pops naked and goes on a quest to unsee what he has seen.

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: A Very Special Blossom/Daylight Savings
added.description: A Very Special Blossom: When the Professor wants an expensive gift for Father's Day, Blossom makes the mistake of taking what she can't afford instead of giving him a gift from the heart./Daylight Savings: The Powerpuff Girls are exhausted in school from saving Townsville past their bedtime. What will happen to their town when the girls are put on a curfew?

added.title: Roughing It Up/What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea?: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

added.title: Prime Mates/Coupe D'Etat
added.description: Prime Mates: Back when Mojo Jojo tried to take over the world with primates, there was one monkey who didn't get his due: Mopey Popo. Now, Mopey is back to try and be just as evil as Mojo intended./Coupe D'Etat: When the Professor tricks out his car, the girls realize that this K.A.R.R. is taking the Professor away from them both figuratively and literally.

added.title: Mo' Linguish/Oops, I Did It Again
added.description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops, I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

added.title: Makes Zen to Me/Say Uncle
added.description: Makes Zen to Me: When Buttercup gets a fortune cookie saying peace lies within, the most violent of Powerpuffs sets out on a quest for inner peace./Say Uncle: The girls' go to pick up the Professor's brother at the train station, but mistake him for a wild-man being transported to the circus.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Sideline Dad
added.description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

added.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
added.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

added.title: Deb O'Nair
added.description: A classy queen of etiquette makes the Utoniums question their superhero way of life.

added.title: Tiara Trouble
added.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

added.title: The Wrinklegruff Gals
added.description: Sick of being the tiniest kids at their new school, the girls convince Professor Utonium to create a potion to make them older! Unfortunately, when they take too much, they become senior citizens and a prime target for Mojo Jojo!

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Bubbles of the Opera
added.description: When Bubbles gets a bad school photo, it sends her into an existential tailspin of darkness.

added.title: Sister Sitter
added.description: When Blossom and Bubbles get sick, Buttercup volunteers to take care of them for the day.

added.title: Odd Bubbles Out
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

added.title: Presidential Punchout
added.description: When Morbucks enters the Student Body President race, Blossom sinks to her level to secure the win.

added.title: Cheep Thrills
added.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: Professor Proofed
added.description: After the Professor's latest experiment goes awry, the girls become overprotective.

added.title: Pool Duel
added.description: Unikitty and the gang are having a great time at the public pool, until they try to get Puppycorn to swim in the deep end with them. Puppycorn is terrified of the deep end. Now Unikitty and the gang must get him over his fear, so he can have maximum pool fun. Meanwhile, Master Frown and Brock are hatching a plan to ruin everyone's fun, by pulling the pool's plug.

added.title: This Spells Disaster
added.description: The gang is planning a surprise for Puppycorn, so they spell things out when talking so he won't find out. Desperate to know what they're saying, Puppycorn finds a magic book that he thinks will help him learn to spell, but unbeknownst to him, it's teaching him how to cast spells! Will Puppycorn realize that knowledge is power and some secrets are kept for a reason?

added.title: Roadtrip Ruckus
added.description: Richard has decided to take Unikitty and the gang for a pleasant and relaxing 10 hour road trip. At first everyone is against the trip, but they soon start to have fun. Unfortunately, their idea of fun is not Richard's.  He soon begins to give in to his inner road-rage. To make matters worse they are being chased by a killer semi-truck, and their car has been invaded by weird bug hitchhiker.  Will Richard loose it, or will the trip be a great success?

added.title: Memory Amok
added.description: When Puppycorn witnesses Unikitty do the most embarrassing thing ever, he vows he will never forget it. Desperate, Unikitty uses Dr. Fox's memory machine to erase Puppycorn's memory of the embarrassing event. In the process, Unikitty accidentally releases all of Puppycorn's memories. Now she and the gang must scramble to capture all the scampering memories, or Puppycorn will forget his life.

added.title: Election Day
added.description: In an effort to prove to Master Frown that she is no tyrant, Unikitty agrees to hold an election to see who will be the new princess of the Unikingdom. In a shock, Master Frown takes an early lead in the poles. Unikitty discovers Frown is winning because he's cheating. Will she resort to her own dirty tricks to win the election or stay true to her self and try to win by being nice?

added.title: No Sleep Sleepover
added.description: It's a sleepover at the castle and Unikitty and Puppycorn want to stay up all night, believing something magical must happen if you stay up long enough.​ At first the friends are game to stay up all night, but as they fall asleep one by one, Unikitty worries they won't make it! How far will she and her bro go to stay awake, and will they discover the secret reason people are supposed to go to bed when the Sandman shows up?

added.title: Unfairgrounds
added.description: Unikitty and her friends have an exciting day at their favorite amusement park/carnival boardwalk but Frown and Brock are there to ruin their good times and drive everyone out! The park owner warns Unikitty that if attendance keeps dropping the pier ​will close forever! Can the friends take charge, save the park, and find out Master Frown's secret ​motives? What a roller coaster of emotions!

added.title: Kitty & Hawk
added.description: When Puppycorn's favorite toy goes missing, Unikitty & Hawkodile team up to track down the thief, buddy-cop style! But when things get tough and the case goes cold, now it's not just their partnership on the line, but their friendship!

added.title: Camp Unikitty
added.description: The gang's set for an awesome weekend of glamorous, easy-living camping out in fun, friendly nature! But when Hawkodile challenges their idea of camping (it should be a fight for survival in the hostile woods), the gang switch places, with Hawkodile living a luxurious glamp life while Unikitty and the others survive in the wild. Will Unikitty still believe the "great outdoors" are all that great if they meet their doom by natural causes?

added.title: Perfect Moment
added.description: When Hawkodile admits his love for Dr. Fox, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings for her. Unfortunately, Unikitty's grand plans for the perfect moment of love complicates everything.

added.title: Hawkodile Sensei
added.description: On a routine mission, Hawkodile finds some defenseless chipmunks that imprint on him.​ ​The bird bodyguard takes it upon himself to become their Sensei teach the younglings his warrior ways, but Unikitty worries his training is too intense. Will Hawkodile's "all work, no play" lifestyle push the chipmunks too far?

added.title: P.L.O.T. Device
added.description: When boredom levels in the castle hit dangerously high levels, Dr. Fox conveniently introduces her P.L.O.T. Device. When pressed, this device alters reality to make it more exciting. Richard warns that this might be dangerous, but no one listens. It's not long till he is proven correct and life in the castle becomes dangerously exciting.

added.title: Who Took Toast
added.description: When Toast disappears from Unikitty's party she leads a search to find him and expose the toast-napper.

added.title: Rainbow Race
added.description: Sadness levels have hit an all-time low in Frowntown. In an attempt to cheer up the citizens of the town, Unikitty and the gang load a rainbow into a tanker truck with the intention of releasing it over Frowntown. Now they must avoid the marauding Master Frown in his monster truck, to succeed.

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Cloris
added.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Merry Moochmas
added.description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

added.title: Pizza Hero
added.description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
